# English-Only Comments & Documentation

- **Comments**: Write all code comments, JSDoc, and inline explanations in **English only**. No Persian/Farsi in comments.
- **Documentation**: README, docblocks, commit messages, and any written explanations in the codebase must be in **English**.
- **Variable/function names**: Keep in English (already standard). No Persian in identifiers.
- **User-facing copy** (e.g. UI labels, error messages shown to users) can follow product/locale requirements separately; this rule applies to **developer-facing** text only (comments, docs, explanations).

Example:

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
// Fetches patient list and invalidates cache on success

// ❌ BAD — do not use non-English (e.g. Farsi, Arabic, etc.) in comments
// fetches and invalidates cache
```
